  </div>

  <div class="phase-info" id="phaseInfo">
    <div class="phase-name" id="phaseName">Healthy Gut Barrier</div>
    <div class="phase-description" id="phaseDesc">
      Tight junctions are sealed. Intestinal cells are connected by claudins, occludin, and other proteins. Only nutrients pass through. Bad stuff stays out.
    </div>
    <div class="phase-details">
      <div class="detail-item" id="detail1">Tight junctions are CLOSED, only letting nutrients through</div>
      <div class="detail-item" id="detail2">Zonulin levels are low (no gap-opening signal)</div>
      <div class="detail-item" id="detail3">Intestinal lining is strong and intact</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="controls">
    <button onclick="gbtPlay()">▶ Play</button>
    <button onclick="gbtSetPhase(0)">⟲ Reset</button>
    <button onclick="gbtSetPhase(0)">Healthy</button>
    <button onclick="gbtSetPhase(50)">Damage</button>
    <button onclick="gbtSetPhase(75)">Leaky</button>
    <button onclick="gbtSetPhase(100)">Heal</button>
  </div>

  <div class="insight-box">
    <strong>The Key Molecule: Zonulin</strong><br>
    Zonulin is a protein released by intestinal cells in response to stress, poor diet, and inflammation. It literally opens the tight junctions like a doorway. When zonulin is high, gaps appear. When it's low, junctions are sealed. Control your zonulin, control your gut barrier.
  </div>
</div>

